\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well there were three brothers and two sisters in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about the number of years between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well the three older ones had about a year and a half between them. 
And then there was Glyn, Cleds father, there was about six years between me and him. And then there was eight years between Glyn and the youngest sister. That\rquote s right, my sister was the - the oldest was a sister and she\rquote 
s still living but the next brother is dead now and Cled\rquote 
s father is dead too. So the ordering was sister, brother, brother, brother, sister. It was a very poor period in those dimes. Bery poor - but then there was a sort of neighbourliness and kindness in the area. You know, we\rquote d be given a
 bag of potatoes or a bag of oatmeal or some buttermilk. And that\rquote s really how we managed to get enough food really. Apart from this kindness we would have been wanting food many times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
