\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh from Traws as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother have a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 I never remember her saying. Her
 hobbies were knitting and crochet. Yes, crochet that was her main thing. And she knitted a lot. She did that all the time I remember her. I\rquote ll tell you what she did, she\rquote 
d start a pair of gloves in the evening say, and somebody wanted them, you know, she got money for doing it, a shilling or so, and she\rquote d finish them by the next morning, she\rquote d have been up all night. Yes, she\rquote 
d knit all through the night just to get this shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember her working at all after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, I\rquote ve no recollection of that but - you see, women didn\rquote 
t in those days. Their home was the most important thing. Yes, she\rquote d knit, oh yes, and she\rquote d go out papering when she was a young girl.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember how many rooms there were in the first house or in the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I remember the first house. No I don\rquote t - I don\rquote 
t remember very much about that at all, I left there when I was three. And I don\rquote t really remember much of the other when, but once we\rquote d grown up to be quite big I remember that 
one perfectly. There were two houses stuck together. And we lived in the back block of it. W}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576 hich}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 was a nearly new house. And it had a small kitchen and the bedroom above the kitchen, and one other bedroom, but it was a very big bedroom. It was a big enough bedroom to make three out of it. And that\rquote 
s where we used to sleep as children. And it didn\rquote t make any difference to the girls or the boys, I mean, we all slept in separate beds in this long bedroom until we got quite big, but there was nothing else - there was nothing else to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did anyone else part from your brothers and sisters and parents live in the house with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, not really, but then we did bury the brother of my mother in a few years and they took one of the children in to bring up.
 And we still regard him as a brother. Yes, he\rquote s in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose} now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nobody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was the washing done in the house or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh - in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother or father make or mend clothes for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, my mother mended the whole lot.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 But your father didn\rquote t?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, he didn\rquote t do anything like that. My father wasn\rquote t any good as a handyman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you buy any second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 hand clothes at all or were they all new?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh I\rquote ll tell you what we had. My mother had a brother in college, one was a schoolmaster and the other went as a chop manager in 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}. And we\rquote d get their clothes and my mother would redo them and - to fit us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 If you had new clothes where would you go to buy them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Well I have no memory - record - before I started working of having new clothes. I never had anything new, I mean - you know, absolutely new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well we had this old aunt, a sister of my father\rquote s. She\rquote 
d married and - quite well and become a widow as a young woman and she was very kind to us. She\rquote d give us shoes and pay for our shoes. I just don\rquote t know how they\rquote d have managed apart from that. But I remember as soon as I start
ed working it was a different story. But before that well I mean I have no record of having - having new shoes, except from this auntie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your father help your mother at all with the housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. No, no, nothing, he worked too long hours. They worked very hard in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he do decorating or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nothing like that, never saw him. Singing was his thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he do anything with you, did he dress or undress you or take you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh he was great for playing with us. He - he just loved playing with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 He used to play with us - play like a pig, you know, he\rquote d go down on all fours and we\rquote d ride on his back. That\rquote 
s the way he used to play with us. He was in his element playing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he tell you stories at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, he just sang. He taught us to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he take you out at all without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - he did - after we got older. We were allowed to go with him to - to fish. He liked fishing. He was a good fisherman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 If your mother went out did he look after you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well yes, yes. But then I mean they couldn\rquote t really afford to go out very much. No, my mother and father couldn\rquote 
t really go very far. My father didn\rquote t bring in much - very much to live on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have any special jobs to do around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, not really for my mother or father, we had to go out and help other people. To earn a penny or so. I\rquote ll t
ell you a story about this. There\rquote s a butche}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  in Traws and I used to go with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You mean round the houses and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, round the houses carrying meat and delivering meat. And then when Saturday came, Saturday night he\rquote d give us a whole 
bag of bones as a sort of reward. They\rquote d be meat bones and they weren\rquote t so fussy about cleaning them and things in those days. And I\rquote d take them back to my mother to make a stew. And we\rquote 
d get enough stew for a week from those. That was instead of shillings
. And then my older brother went out to work for the farmers and my sister went out to - be a servant girl, - to do for people. Everybody did what they could to get something in to get food. That was the big problem.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your sisters have things to do around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Well - there was quite a big difference between the sisters. Yes, my older sister was a bit peeved when my younger sister was born because she had to help my mother. But she was a great singer and she went out a lot with my father,
 the oldest one. To win - we\rquote ve won a lot of things singing.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576  singing,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did the older children help the younger children with things that they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, they did, but we were - yes, we were like two families really. The three oldest on
es had been brought up together. And then Glyn came and there was a gap and then there was Betty. And that gap really sort of separated this - all the time I mean I knew they were brothers and sisters }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid28231\charrsid11292576 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ut there was a gap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did the younger children help you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Well, you see, the trouble was that the older children always got the blame for everything that the younger children did. I mean, you must know that from your experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they actually help you with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, not really because I\rquote d gone away to work to be a farm labourer before - they were old enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, very strict. Except on the night of the Band of Hope or the night of the Sayat. Yes, they were very keen chapel goers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I mean the memory I have is going to bed on my own. They\rquote 
d just say, go to bed, and off you sent. But remember to wash before you go to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How old were you when that happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh about six. And my older sister\rquote d be nine going on ten and we\rquote d help each other. Go to bed together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And you shared your bedroom with the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, there were three - there were two beds and then my older brother shared with Glyn and then there }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576 was my sister. Oh it was an eno}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
rmous bedroom. But as we got older my mother put a curtain across between my sister and the rest of us. Once she - once my sister was about eight. And so she divided the room up with a curtain, but I mean it didn\rquote t ma
ke much difference, we still kept riots - had riots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you mean chatting through the curtains and that? And did your mother and father have a separate room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes, they had another bedroom, the other bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Where did you have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 In front of the fire. Yes, that\rquote s right, in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How often did you have to have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Every Saturday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When did you have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh every Saturday again - Saturday night. To prepare for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Where did the family eat their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh in the kitchen. There was only the kitchen and the scullery and the parlour downstairs. Yes, I mean the kitchen was used for everything really, we didn\rquote t go into the parlour.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was there any special occasion when you did eat in the parlour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, in the kitchen. Yes, we had a great big grate you know, the old type with a - an oven and a boiler.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You mean with the fire underneath the oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, what I mean - the fire was in the middle and the oven and the - boiler were separate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What time did you have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Now wait a minute, we lived quite far from the school, we had about a twenty minute walk to school so we had to
 get up fairly early. But my father, obviously he got up about five. And my mother got up before five every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You mean she got up to make breakfast for your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes. Yes. To start him off to work. But then she\rquote d come back to bed afterwards and we\rquote d be called about 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past seven{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you usually have to eat or drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well it really depended what there was, we often had stew. I mean, there wasn\rquote 
t much sort of picking and choosing to be had. We ate what we could. And we\rquote d have buttermilk and bread. And then for a treat we\rquote d have a little pudding or something. My mother was a great cook. She was a really good cook, I mean, she
\rquote d make meals out of the weirdest thing. I mean, there\rquote s no tinned foods to be had in those days. You had to cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have anything special for breakfast say on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no, no, nothing, it was the same. We had a good dinner though on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What time did you have dinner as a rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well, about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}midday{\*\xmlclose} or {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 12}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past twelve
{\*\xmlclose}. We\rquote d come home from school - we\rquote d walk home from school. We didn\rquote t have dinners in school. In a way we had to run to get home and get back to school in time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Your father was working, did he take a tin of food for lunch to the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, he did. And I\rquote ll tell you what his favourite feed was, a raw onion. He\rquote 
d take a raw onion with him every day if he could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you usually have to eat at dinner time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well that really depended on what my mother had managed to get from the farmer. We\rquote 
d get plenty of buttermilk. And as children we liked what we called}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576  spoon-foods, foods which you at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 e with a spoon and we\rquote 
d get these sort of things, gruels and things, very often. I mean, it was home cooking or whatever you call it. Because I mean nothing was really bought because there wasn\rquote t any money to buy it with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you get your main meal in the evening when your father got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, we didn\rquote t. No, we had dinner when we had dinner but - and you see we\rquote d gone 
to bed by the time my father got home. My father didn\rquote t get home \lquote til - well the - the train reached Traws about {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 17}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}five to seven - twenty to seven{\*\xmlclose} and it was nearly seven by the time he got home and - well we were in bed by then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember what your father had to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh my mother was very good at attending to my father. He was a very big man and he worked very hard and she was very good at making food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your father or mother bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, everything, my mother did - all of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she bottle fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, she didn\rquote t bottle so much, she wasn\rquote t really done in th-ose days, it\rquote s a newer thing. No she mainly made jam.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she make pickles and wine and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. Oh she made every sort of wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she make medicine at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - blackberry wine was the greatest medicine - when you had a cold. And she made elderberry wine too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she make any beer at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no, nothing like that. My mother was a fantastic teetotaler. But my father wasn\rquote 
t a teetotaler. And I think I really took after my mother \lquote cos I\rquote m a - fantastic teetotaler too. Oh yes, I am.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother or father grow fruit or vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, they didn\rquote 
t but the only thing I do remember is my father was allowed to plant a row of potatoes because we lived in the country a bit. He\rquote d plant a row of potatoes here and there and go and help and my mother would go and help on the farm - i
n the hay. And you see, they were allowed - I mean I wouldn\rquote 
t say that they ever bought a single potatoes, they got all their potatoes from the farms around. You see, in return for helping farmers the people who helped were allowed to plant a row of potatoes in the farmer\rquote s land.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they have to buy other vegetables and things in the shops, cabbages and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well no, I don\rquote t really remember that. The only thing I remember is s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid28231\charrsid11292576 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 edes, swedes were the thing then. That was the main food then. Swedes and carrots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And there was nothing tinned or dried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, I don\rquote t ever remember opening a tin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your family keep any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, my mother kept hens. And you should have heard her, it\rquote d be great to get a record of her ta
lking to the hens. There was a big wood near where we used to live and when we were old enough children we\rquote d climb }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
p into the trees and listen to my mother talking to the hens. Haven\rquote t you laid you bitch? Maybe you\rquote d better cross this out. I\rquote m only really saying it in passing. And you know she\rquote 
d talk to them, she knew very well which hen had laid an egg and which hen hadn\rquote t. And she\rquote d go up to them and she\rquote d say, haven\rquote t you laid yet you bitch? And we\rquote d be above her in the trees listening. And we\rquote 
d laugh until we were rolling around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember how often in a week you\rquote d have meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well in - on}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid28231\charrsid11292576 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 y Sunday. And then I mean not every Sunday. Sometimes my father would have got a hare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he poach at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, he just happened to be good at getting them. No, he was a good fisherman and what happened, he\rquote 
d catch a lot of fish and share them out and then somebody else would come back with a rabbit or a hare in the winter to repay him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 He didn\rquote t do any sort of poaching at all then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you ever remember seeing your mother having less food in order that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, very well. I\rquote ve said many times since then that I\rquote m sure my mother went to bed on many nights without havin
g food, in order that she could keep the food until morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she give it to your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, she\rquote d give it to him in the morning or to the children before they went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Were you allowed to talk at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. They weren\rquote t strict like that at all. But if my father said then everybody knew it was full stop and everybody shut up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, there was no choice, we ate what we got. Or we\rquote d be without it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did your parents feel if you left some food uneaten on your plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well actually I\rquote ve no recollection of it ever happening, because the food wasn\rquote 
t that plentiful and everyone welcomed it and was thankful for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 If there was somet
hing on the table that you wanted, like the salt, were you allowed to ask someone to pass it or wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh - well the things was that everything started with my father, and very often it was my oldest sister that sat next to
 my father and my older brother next and it went like that you see. In rotation like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And everyone always sat in the same place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, everyone had their place at the table. And my mother sat on the other side of the table next to the teapot. And actually that
\rquote s one thing I never saw my father do. I never saw him pour - pouring out the tea. No. I mean, you know, take me for instance, well I pour out the tea quite often, and wash the dishes and things, but I - I never saw him do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have second helpings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh yes, we did - I mean if the food was available we did. But then things were tight sometimes and we had to share it out very carefully. And I mean it was always my mother who suffered but, I mean, she\rquote d say nothing, she was quite quiet about it.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they expect you to hold your knife and took in a particular way or sit in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well, no, I mean you had to behave, but there was no sort of - I mean, it was quite plain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You didn\rquote t have fancy manners or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nothing of the sort. But when my father said no it was no. There was no point in thinking after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Could you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 bring toys or books to the table during mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Could you leave the table when you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no. No. You had to be quite civil. You had to behave properly or there was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 doubt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 . And it was a clout, we\rquote d no nonsense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Who served your meal, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes. Mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember what order you were served in? Your father got served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, it was always like that. My father was head of the family and he kept his place. And I\rquote 
ll tell you something, he had this old wooden armchair, bigger than t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 e one we\rquote 
ve got in the front, and say I was sitting in his chair and unless you went from there without him saying a single word - look out. You\rquote d really made a mistake, it was a - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 
unforgivable}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  sin nearly. And so we only had to see my father coming through the door and we were out of there immediately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember where your younger sister and brother sat before they were able to feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well they had a sort of priv}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 lege next }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  my mother. You see, we\rquote 
d be behind the table and my mother and the younger children would be - the other 
side as it were. Yes, you see, after the three first children my mother got some peace for a bit, it was nearly - five nearly six years before Glyn came along and then eight years again from Glyn and Bettey. Between Glyn and Betty. So we were - we helped 
each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, she was and she talked well too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, she forfeited everything for the children and her husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 If you had any - worry at all were you able to share it with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well the thing was it was school that was the only thing we really had on our mind. We felt we weren\rquote t learning quick enough.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was your father easy to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, the e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 siest in the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he show affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. And he could be as wild as a match but - no, no, I mean - he was great. Very affectionate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did your parents feel that you ought to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - they - they felt we should obey and if you didn\rquote t do that you\rquote d
 had it. Specially my father, he was very strict like that. If he told you to go he expected you to go like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your parents bring you up to behave in a certain way towards your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 I don\rquote t re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 lly think they did, except that the main thing was that we had to be friends and share things with each other. If we didn\rquote t get on, you know, look out. And you know I\rquote 
m afraid that nowadays things have changed too quickly to the other side. Be}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ore children are able to accept these th
ings, children just expect things nowadays, and they don\rquote t think anybody - they don\rquote t owe anything to anybody. I mean, that\rquote s a fact isn\rquote t it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 If another child hit you were you allowed to hit him back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, we were, I mean they didn\rquote t really 
take any interest in things like that. Any notice. I mean, if two children were fighting I mean my mother and father\rquote d say nothing, they knew they\rquote d be friends again within the hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember what type of person your parents hoped you\rquote d grow up to be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
No, the only thing my father hoped, and I heard him say this many times, I remember when I went out to work, my sister and me and my brother, he said, listen, if the master tells you to take some cow dung and dump it in the river you do it. 
You obey. That was the point. To be obedient to people, but not to be servile. He said that all the time. Don\rquote t be servile but be - be obedient. There\rquote s a limit to obedience isn\rquote 
t there. That was something that was emphasised by him greatly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 So really it was obedience that your parents felt the most important thing in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh yes, obedience, and there is another thing, I never heard them fighting. And if there ever was a disagreement we had to get out of there, \lquote cos these things were sorted out without the children, so they couldn\rquote t hear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Were you allowed to swear at all in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. We weren\rquote t. I\rquote m not saying we didn\rquote t do it often but - but we were punished if we did in their hearing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When adults were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, not at all. It was out of the question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well there was often a punishment. The cupboard under the stairs was the goal in those days. Yes, we went in - u
nder the stairs. And they put you in there when it was time for you to go and play somewhere else. So it hit in two ways. I mean, you know, it was two things, I mean, just to be in the cupboard under the stairs was enough of a punishment but when you reme
mbered the others were out playing you had two punishments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And did your mother and father do this to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. And the other thing is, if my mother said something my father never kept our part. That\rquote 
s how it was supposed to be. Because I know on many occasion he wasn\rquote t of her opinion only they stuck together, because my mother was a bit of a nagger. She nagged the children, go - go and go. But my father didn\rquote 
t. He just said go, and you went. And if you didn\rquote t you\rquote d be clouted. But that sort of thing didn\rquote t happen because you did go. We knew what the consequences were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember a particular occasion on which you were punished and how did you feel towards this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I don\rquote t remember being punished so that it hurt. If you were pu
nished - you forgot about it and tried not to do it again. You tried not to go through the same thing twice. If you wanted to make mischief you did different naughty things so you didn\rquote t get the same punishment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 . I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 tell you, this is the worst punishment we used to have, the greatest sin was to be late coming home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you mean coming home from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, from the village. I mean, we could go to the Band of Hope and to the Sayar and we could play, but if it passed quarter to seven they
\rquote d start asking you around because - my mother wanted to clear the children out of the way before my father came in from work, the old children that is, they\rquote d gone out of the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you think you received the ideas you have about how to behave from your father o
r mother, or do you feel that one had more influence than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Well, in the end my father had an authority, the influence, although he made much less noise about it. And I think it was his things that have sort of - taken a hold of me more than anything - anyone. I\rquote 
ve got no time for somebody who nags all the time. I can\rquote t bear somebody nagging, nagging. If somebody tells me to do something I do it and I expect children to do the same. It\rquote s the only thing I\rquote ve got against children today. They wa
nt an argument, instead of, you know, when you say something they just go off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was your birthday a different day from other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no. Wasn\rquote t - was no difference at all. I mean, I knew it was my birthday, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You didn\rquote t have anything special or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well we did sometimes have pancakes, specially after we got older we had pancakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You didn\rquote t have toy or presents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nothing. I don\rquote t ever remember myself having anything like that. But I do remembe
r getting a penknife and that was a present. \lquote Cos I really liked carving and when I got this penknife it was first class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember anything special about Christmas Day, you\rquote re your mother or father do anything particular with you together?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well singing was the main point in our family. My father was really keen on singing
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well not until we began to win. But none when we were little children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Who sung all together in the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh well, everybody sang. I had quite a good soprano voice when I was a boy. And then there was Owen and - we had to sing soprano all the time in order to keep the choir going as it were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your parents play games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, we used to play hide and seek and things. But not in the house. We\rquote d go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You\rquote ve already said that your father played pigs with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, my father was really in his element with this pig game. And the other thing he used to do particularly with Betty - I - I\rquote 
d be working by this time - was to put her in the wheelbarrow with Glyn and take the two out for a ride in the wheelbarrow. And I don\rquote t know where he got the energy from either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Were there books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes. Yes. A lot
 of them were musical books. But as we got older, specially with my brother, was very keen on reading. But, you know, when we were small the school really was the main source of our education.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Wha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 t about newspapers, do you remem}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ber if you had newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, we used to get the - the Rhedegydd. The Runner or Courier. That was the only - it was a local paper, that was the only one we got.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no, there\rquote s nothing like that. I mean, the thing was that there wasn\rquote t any
 money because you - look at it like this I mean, four and three was all my father earned in a day in the quarry. Now share that out between a family of five children, there wasn\rquote t very much to spare was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you ever remember your father or mother reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. My mother and father. My father liked reading a lot, and my mother too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they read aloud at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, my mother loved reading out aloud to us. Yes, my mother liked it. I mean, the Bible was the main thing - the ma
in book in that time really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, I don\rquote 
t really when I was small at all, but when I got older I remember burying my grandmother and far away relatives I remember when I was become a child of - when I had become a child of ten.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember who attended these funerals? Were there a lot of people there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, there weren\rquote t. I mean, funerals were popular things but nothing like today. People couldn\rquote t really afford to lose 
work at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they wear mourning clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11891628\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 lack was very important in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about armbands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. And thing is, I mean, even today, I mean, I put on a black tie, even if the person isn\rquote t actually r
elated to me when I go to a funeral. It\rquote s something that\rquote s sort of stuck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your parents take you to visit friends, neighbours and relatives at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, not really. But I mean by the time we were eight we had to go and help out. Run messages for people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you go shopping with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well now we did the shopping. Because since our home was outside the village we\rquote 
d get instructions when we came home from - came home for dinner, we had to bring groceries back for my mother at tea time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you ever go out alone with our father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well the main attraction was the chapel and we went to chapel my father came with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember going for trips or outings with your parents or holidays at Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 I remember going with my mother to see a cousin in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}
. Oh I was very young, then, I got lost there. I don\rquote t remember where I was but I was going kup this street kicking a ball in front of me and the ball rolled away and that was enough to make me get lost. I remember that quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you ever go away for a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Never. Before I started working. Only that time we were in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}Liverpool{\*\xmlclose}
 and we were only there for a day hen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Could you tell me how you spent your Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - the main thing we did was to go and collect the milk on the Saturday. We\rquote 
d go about two times a week so on Saturday morning we\rquote d go to collect the milk. And me and Sean and - Noel used to go. And Noel and Sean had to carry a bundle of sticks b
ack with them and I carried the milk as I was the youngest of the three. I got a lot of affection because I was the younger of the three and the others got lots of beatings because of me too. I did the bad things and the others got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you spend Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - if we had good enough clothes we\rquote d go to the chapel. But then may be people didn\rquote 
t have different clothes for chapel or - no shoes or - something like that. But if we did have reasonable clothes, or may be two of us had decent clothes and the other didn\rquote t, and then he\rquote 
d have to stay at home and the others went to the chapel and - prayed well. And that\rquote s really what ruled a lot of the family activities. I don\rquote t know, things have changed. For the better I suppose but we don\rquote t sometimes see that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Were you allowed to play on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, we were, but we did it on the sly really. It didn\rquote t please at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your parents think it was wrong?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - they weren\rquote t really strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about working on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no, none of that was done at all. Not as a rule anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your parents go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, my father was a very keen chapel goer. My father looked after the chapel in fact. He looked after the lamps, he lighted the lamps.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Which chapel was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh the Trawsfynydd Methodist chapel. In fact I was there the other day burying someone and I saw the man going round lighting the lamps and the candles, p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 raffin lamps, that\rquote s right, he used to the candle to light the p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 raffin lamps.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How often would you say your father went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - he never missed Sunday school. He loved his Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about you, did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, we had to go didn\rquote t we. That\rquote s all there was to it, we had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember any social activities that you took part in which were organized by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, not really, I was a singer then, I used to sing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Were you in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, there wasn\rquote t a choir. No there wasn\rquote t really. It was the Band of Hope, I learnt the so-fah there but I really didn
\rquote t learn so-fah the way I should have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 So you went to the Bank of Hope?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And then I went to the Sayat too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What sort of things did you do there, apart from singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, you learnt to recite. To read. Yes, you had to learn verses and things. But I wasn\rquote 
t really clever enough to to that, I didn\rquote t learn to read until I\rquote d left school. Especially English.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you belong to any other sort of clubs belonging to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. There wasn't anything else. The chapel was just the main centre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you say grace before meals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, we didn\rquote t do that. But we never went to bed without going on our knees, that was certain. Because I mean once you\rquote 
ve been conditioned to do that you can\rquote t not. I mean if you learnt - you teach a child young enough it just comes to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have family prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, there was nothing like that. No, my father and mother weren\rquote t that - that dry, like it was in those 
days. You know it was a sin to laugh in those days hen you were in a certain position. In fact laughter meant that you were lost to the world.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your father take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, I mean, he was - completely potty about it. He was Labour ever since I can remember. And he was very god at arguing the point.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you agree with your father in his ideas?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well actually if you - once you\rquote ve been - you\rquote d been through that period you couldn\rquote t not. The period squeezed you 
into realizing that your father had been cross, done down. The way in which the parents had had to bring up a family. I\rquote ll tell you a story. We lived out of the village and - and ounce of tobacco was four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 pence in those days and my father really liked an ounce of tobacco and he didn\rquote t have any money and he\rquote d say, can you lend me a ha\rquote 
penny Mary, to his wife, in order to get half an ounce of tobacco? Tuppence ha\rquote penny. He paid tuppence ha\rquote penny for half an ounce. Well may be we had a ha\rquote penny in our pockets,
 been given it for doing something for somebody, but we wouldn\rquote t give that because we\rquote d have to go down and fetch the tobacco. It meant a twenty minutes or half an hour journey for us. But we\rquote 
d give it to my mother when we went to bed and my father would get his half ounce of tobacco in Blaenau the next morning. That\rquote s a story, I\rquote ll always remember that forever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember why your father held the political views that he did hold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well it was because he\rquote d been brought up very hard. He\rquote d worked very very hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember your father and mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, I don\rquote t remember. I tell you the only thing\rquote s that stuck in my mind before 1919 was the Coronation in 1911 wasn
\rquote t it, with George V or something. That\rquote s really the only thing I can say I remember well before 1919. Well really before I started working. But then I did start working at eight, when I was eight years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Could you say what political party your parents belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well they were Labour but it was Liberal I think in those days, there was no Labour candidate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And presumably they became Labour as soon as there was a candidate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes. Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 At that time in some places men felt that they risked losing the
ir job or their house if they voted in a different way from their employers, do you ever remember your father feeling this kind of pressure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, I don\rquote t think he did. I mean he was a man who wasn\rquote t afraid of work and I don\rquote t think he ever got the sac
k. But I knew - I mean, I knew this sort of thing went on there\rquote s no doubt about that. But my father was a very independent man, and I remember him even leaving the quarry over an argument and just chancing his luck - just chancing his luck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was your father a member of any political party, did he belong to the Labour party?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, in the last years he did. But I don\rquote t remember anything form the first years. Politics weren\rquote 
t quite the same then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember himsworking for a particular 
time at the time of a general election? Or did he do any political work outside the elections?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Yes, I mean the main thing he did was in the quarry in the - eating cabin. He was very good at sort of warning young people to be careful about what}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 they did, he was a great favourite with young people always and he taught - twenties of young boys to be rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 men and they were happy to learn with him. He was very keen, I mean, I worked with him for a bit and he was very keen to teach boys. And I mean that\rquote s what he did, that\rquote 
s what he believed in, in passing on his knowledge to the young peo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 le and he\rquote 
s say this, you know, about the chapel too. And he\rquote d alwa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 ys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 say that if the chapel did as half as much as it preached it did then it would really be quite influential. In showing people the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother belong to any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, my mother was very quiet. She didn\rquote 
t make any fuss about anything. But she was very neighbourly. Yes, my father really, he did most of his political work and general sense outside the general election time, in the work place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When your parents weren\rquote t working how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well my father had his}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 singing as his main thing. He conducted - he was a conductor for years and there was a choir practice well about twice a week but my mother - knitting, that\rquote s what she liked doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Not many. She didn\rquote t go out and enjoy herself at all, no. No, not to any sort of social activities or anything. Except som
etimes she\rquote d go home and visit her mother. My grandmother was a nurse, but she\rquote d had a stroke when she was a young girl and - my mother\rquote d sometimes go over as my - as her brothers and sisters and did to see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When did your father come in from work at night? Did you say quarter past seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, quarter to seven. That\rquote s when the train arrived in Traws. And he arrived home at seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he spend his evenings at home or did he go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well he tended to - stay in but quite often there was a singing practice in our house, if there was go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ng to be a concert or anything like that they came round to our house and practiced. And then other times he\rquote 
d go to some piano somewhere else. In fact really he was away quite a lot in the evenings.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did he go to any clubs or pu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 s at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, very rarely. I don\rquote t remember him doing it at all when I was small. But I knew he wasn\rquote 
t in fact a teetotaler. But I\rquote ll tell you one thing, he wouldn\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  spend his four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 pence knowing that we wanted food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Your mother didn\rquote t often go out then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no. Not, no, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your father take part in sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, not really, but when there was this freeze up in the quarry I saw him skating or sliding on the river, \lquote cos the}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 river was all frozen over of course. And it wasn\rquote t only him either but other men. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 Quite a lot, because there were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 eighty to a hundred men from Traws who worked in the quarries in Llan Ffestiniog, so you can imagine that the rive was pretty covered w
ith people. I remember this today. My father was a great big man and he fell flop on the river and the ice cracked right across and everyone was shouting in case he went down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember him going to the races at all? Or betting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, no. And he never bet a single shilling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother or father belong to any sort of savings clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, there was no - no one had heard of that sort of thing then. Because people - working people didn\rquote 
t have much money to save.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they have any sort of sick insurance or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, in the quarry they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You mean with the trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, with that. Yes, he had one of those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about collecting money for a funeral or something, was there any sort of club for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nothing. There was a sort of ins}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11414956\charrsid11292576 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 rance and you paid about a penny a week or something and that could be used for anything.
