\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember how you felt towards the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 There was no difference at all. The only thing was, I mean, he wasn\rquote t so good on repairs but
 - and one half of the house was absolutely new and there w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15811538\charrsid11292576 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ren\rquote 
t many repairs to do on it. It was very difficult to get repairs done. And the reason really was that the man was pretty poor himself. Except that he just happened to have been able to get this house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You said your family had difficulty in making ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. Yes, we did. And many times I remember that. And there was many other families apart from them in that period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you feel towards this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 I think you know i
n a way we - we - we accepted it. But you know when somebody did give you something it made you thankful, more thankful. I mean, say we went to a farm place nearby - I never remember getting a penny from him, I never had a penny from him, but I carried ar
mfuls of potatoes away from there, and you know, you felt that that was a help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You also said it was a very hard time when your father wasn\rquote t working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 There was - no, because there was nothing. There was only - charity if you wanted something. And I can\rquote 
t ever remember us accepting charity at all, because you see my mother\rquote s brothers happened to be very intelligent boys and they\rquote 
d worked themselves up and they were very kind to her. And the only time he was out out of work was when the quarries froze up. Oh yes, yes, I don\rquote t remember him out of work apart from that. But I r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15811538\charrsid11292576 emember him working short hours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 - short times, three days a week say, in 1913. They worked three days a week in those days. And that was the time which they widened the road out here, they\rquote d work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15811538\charrsid11292576 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 d three days in the quarry and three days on this road and they did the same thing in Traws as well. You know that big hill that goes up towards the station in Traws, that was widened in 1913. And
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And do you know why there was this shut down in the quarries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh - well - it was sl-ck you see, they couldn\rquote 
t sell the - the slates because the war was coming in Germany and Germany had stopped buying up the slate, and that meant that, you know, you would only get three days work there a week.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
If there was someone in your area that people disapproved of very much was there any special way of showing this disapproval? Do you ever remember somebody having to leave the area because people had made a great noise ou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15811538\charrsid11292576 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 side the house, rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. No, no, I can\rquote t. I don\rquote t think so. But I\rquote ll tell you what - happened if you weren\rquote 
t sort of in favour. Ev}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5908187\charrsid11292576 eryone would i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 gnore you. I don\rquote 
t know why but it seemed natural. I mean, say there was a man with - unruly thoughts or an unruly mind, everyone would cut him out because, you know, I mean - and the chapel was the centre and the two things worked together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember any effigies being made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - I mean - there were occasions when a man would try and make out that he was more than a man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 But you don\rquote t remember straw men being carried through the streets as a caricature of someone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Only - the only Coronation that I can remember - ever remember, a sort of parade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember getting any lessons from your parents or private tutors at all before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well we\rquote d have reading lessons at home because my mother liked reading and she liked us to read }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I should think I was five - turned five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When you first started school what time did you leave in the morning to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh by nine, we had to be there by nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What type of school was it, was it a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, it wasn\rquote t but there was a church school in Traws at that time. Yes, it was a primary school if that\rquote 
s what you mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was it mixed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, it had girls and boys. I\rquote 
ll tell you something funny about those days, you see there were very big boys in our class in standard four and standard five and standard three and there was a partition between standard three and standard four and I\rquote 
d see these great big boys sitting by the door in prayers in the morning and I\rquote d see them always. And they were there and we were so much littler, you see, I didn\rquote 
t understand why they were there. And the thing was I thought, you know, that the big boys were stupid or something otherwise he\rquote d have to, you know, leave school years before. But the thing was I mean he just happened - those people 
just happened to be luckier in their parents then I was, and they\rquote d been allowed to stay on at school. Because I mean the things was that with workers children when they came to thirteen or even twelve they\rquote 
d slacken off going to school and go out to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And you walked to school and it took you about twenty minutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes. I mean either fifteen or twenty minutes, depending on whether - you know, I walked fast or slow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you go alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no, no, three of us went together and sometimes the neighbouring farm children came too and we all went together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You went home to get food at midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes, we always went home. And the only time that we didn\rquote 
t go home to get food because my grandmother lived at the back of the school and if my grandmother had had a letter from one of the children that was away she\rquote 
d call for my brother and I could follow him in his shadow and go there to such dinner in order that he could read my grandmother\rquote s letter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 She was completely illiterate was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, she was. I mean she was illiterate but - you know, I\rquote 
m sure she could read her Bible. But reading a letter was something, you know, quite different. And my brother was a fantastic reader and she\rquote d stand behind him as he was reading and when he\rquote d finished she\rquote 
d say, you read like a parson. She felt that, you know, there wasn\rquote t - other people - people apart from the parson shouldn\rquote t really be able to read. That was her idea. Yes, she said, you read like a parson. And we\rquote d get dinner
 after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you feel about the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh you know, I was never angry towards it because, you know, the thing was I sort of happened to be a favourite with the teachers all the time. I don\rquote t know why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you feel towards the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh I got on you know very well with the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did the teachers emphasise some things as being important in life, like manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, manners. Manners were the first thing in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 Oh - oh, yes, pu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
nctuality, that was important. I should say actually that these are the three most important things, going to chapel, keeping time, being on time and being mannerly and I think that manners have gone to the wrong place at the moment. They\rquote 
ve gone to the back rather than being at the front. But they did teach you that, you had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they emphasise of ways of speaking, did you have to speak pure Welsh for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, we did. They emphasised th
at fantastically. There was very little English in school in those days and I never really mastered English. I never learnt to spell English, but you know, Welsh spelling well I did that all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What happened if you did something which the teachers disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh it was the cane in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they used the same punishment on girls and boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - it was - as a rule it was the boys that got the blame for things. And ordinarily it was actually the boys that had actually done
 it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What sort of things had they done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Making faces at the teacher for instance. And look out after that. Pulling our tongue on the teacher. I mean, that was worse than if you swore because doing that meant that you\rquote d lost your manners and that was a great sin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your parents take an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, my mother was - terrible like that. But my father wasn\rquote t really, he didn\rquote t have time. It was work for him then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your mother ask what you\rquote d been doing at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, she\rquote d ask and you know she was interested in everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she go up to the school at all to see the teachers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, only one or two people used to do that. If they felt that one of their children was being crossed. But it r
arely happened that parents went up to the school I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Would you say the children you were at school with were from the same background as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes, ordinarily they were. But there was a - a group. Well you know there was Doctor Williams\rquote 
 school in Dolgellan at that time which was important to girls, when they reached nine or ten years old and if they were in that sort of social position they\rquote d - you know - leave the primary school and go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And that was a private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Yes, yes, a private school. I mean, you know, to us as workers well, I mean, everyone was the same. But if you were a scholar, I remember well, as there were in school in those days and I think if had learnt English properly, and I never learnt to spell 
in English, but you know I was fantastic at sums and they picked you out, they\rquote d make you specialize and you know make you do things that you were clever at rather than make you pick up on things that you weren\rquote 
t so good at and of course you got worse in those things. Yes, they made you specialize where you were bright. And you know I think that that has sort of - become a lot better today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember the teachers selecting some people for different treatment from others? You\rquote ve already said that 
you were a favourite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, I was, I don\rquote t know why. I\rquote m not saying you know that I - I\rquote 
m proud of myself, but I was good at making acquaintances and, you know, if somebody asked me to do something I\rquote d go away immediately and do it. And I think that that was what did it you know, we\rquote 
d been taught that way at home and so we were off you know and in the end that pays off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember there being gangs or groups in the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, at that time standard four, standard three, standard
 two, standard one were together. And there would be a group from standard one and a group from standard two and those stood out and then there\rquote 
d be a group from standard four. I was with the - the older groups would look down on the younger groups and wouldn\rquote t play with them because they were younger than them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember some children being left out of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No I don\rquote t think I remember that ever happening. But some people were picked on if they were sinners. You know, you were the on
e that did everything wrong, and I think there was quite a lot of that then whereas there isn\rquote t today.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You never went on to a different school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, I didn\rquote t.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I got a job with a doctor in Traws.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When did you first start going to afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
I went - I went all the time, I mean ever since I started school. I went to school in the afternoon, we left at three - three thirty. Yes, I was telling you about getting a job with the doctor in Traws. I got a job looking after the doctor\rquote 
s horse. That must have been in 1916. And I could leave at school at thirteen in January. But the education authorities found out. If I hadn\rquote t gone to the farmers and I had to go back to schoo
l. They said I had to go back to school or go to the farmers. And you\rquote ll never be able to appreciate the shame that that was. Even though I liked farming very much. But going to look after the Doctor\rquote 
s horse, well that was a sort of privilege. Only I had to go to the farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 Do you think you would have st}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ayed longer at school if you\rquote 
d had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Yes, I think I would. But you know I mean learning is nothing unless you can get food in your stomach. That was the point you see. And we went out as children a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 nd we were lucky enough to get 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 given food by people. Otherwise we\rquote 
d have been wanting terribly. And many people find it difficult to believe that workers children did, you know, really lack food and want food. And suffered because of it. I mean a lot of people today say, oh it was their fault, they didn\rquote 
t try to work and things like that but you know in those days there were men who worked long hours, yes, long hours. Saturdays and everything and were still wanting food after that because they didn\rquote t get enough to live on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you take part in any part time e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ucation after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. No, no, I didn\rquote 
t. -The thing was I - straight after I left school I went out to become a farm labourer in a far sway farm, and I didn\rquote t ge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  the opportunity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You never went to night}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 school or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. Nothing. Except that I have been, you know, once or twice after I married. But as far as I know, I mean, after I married it\rquote 
s been my wife who\rquote s been the best help in teaching me to read English.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you regret anything about your education?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. No, I don\rquote t think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you think it did you good to go to school, that you benefited from it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - it taught me one thing. To respect other people. And I think you know that\rquote s the best thing I\rquote 
ve ever learnt. Being polite to people. You see, there are two things, there\rquote s being polite and being servile, two quite different things and my father emphasised that a lot. I mean, to respect people properly but only so far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When you were at school did you have any part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I used to go to work, I mean, I used to go to the farm when I was a boy of eight. I didn\rquote 
t go home after school. I went straight to the farm where I\rquote d have my tea and I\rquote d go from there to school in the next morning. And that way I\rquote d get my food. And I only got my food. I\rquote 
d help getting coal for the morning and chopping wood - firewood. And sort of things like that. And I did that for two or three terms. And I remember
 this old boy, I mean, I told you I never got a penny from him, he gave me a bag of basic slag or a basic slag bag, and he said, take this bag and fill it and take it back to your mother full of potatoes. I filled it but I couldn\rquote 
t get over the wall with it. I had to go and fetch my father to car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 y it. I remember that today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you get this job, through your parents or did you hear about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well the things was that I was - I was very friendly with the Doctor\rquote s servant and I\rquote d go to see him 
in the stable, the stable was very near our village and I was in my element with the horse. And I also happened to be friends with the Doctor\rquote 
s housekeeper - I was a great favourite with her. And the old doctor was more shameful than I was when I had to leave because he\rquote d tried every way to get me, but I couldn\rquote 
t until I was fourteen. You know, you could go on the farm but - and that\rquote s what I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How many hours did you work in the part time job that you sid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I say it was four when you got h
ome from school, four to half past and you had tea ad then it was time to milk and, you know, you started to collect things for the morning. Bring the coal and the firewood. And then there was sort of jobs like peeling potatoes, I did - that a lot in the 
evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 There weren\rquote t holidays with pay with this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nothing. Except that you did, you know, once you were a farm labourer, if yu\rquote 
d been with a farm for six months, after six months you\rquote d get a week off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How much did you get paid for your part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - no - yes, you didn\rquote t get your - a wage really, I mean, maybe you\rquote 
d get the odd shilling or something but you know the first term I went to be a farm labourer I remember exactly how much I got. And the other thing we did in those days was to go out and make hay in the hay season. And we\rquote 
d carry hay with the horses. And you\rquote d stack the hay on the cart as it whizzed by and you know you\rquote d get, well, about two - two weeks work or something and you\rquote d get your food with that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you feel that the money you got for doing the part time job was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 Well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  you didn\rquote 
t think about it in those terms really. You were glad of what you got. I mean, maybe you\rquote d just get a piece of cake from some people. A lump of cake. It was 
a different age. I mean, take today, if somebody comes to do some work for you today you give him a pound note and he\rquote s no more thankful. He isn\rquote t. I mean that\rquote 
s a fact. With the money, I mean - I mean, you felt that it was a privilege to do things then. I\rquote ll tell you one thing that was different then too was that nobody had a water tap and you\rquote 
d carry the water from the wells and this was carried hundreds of buckets of water up from the well. For lots of different people, sometimes I\rquote d carry the water into the kitchen. And you\rquote d do it regularly and they\rquote 
d pay you every month say, they\rquote d give you a shilling or so for carrying water for a month. That was sort of separate employment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you give the money you got to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, I gave everything to my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did she spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well, anything to get a bit of food. And ordinarily if she had a little bit over she\rquote 
d buy an ounce of wool or something because she loved knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you get on with the other people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes. Fine every time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did your employers treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Well - exactly the way you treated them. If you were fair, and to be fair now, I mean I got - every - everyone I worked for was pretty fair to me as long as you trie
d to do the things that you were supposed to do. I mean there was no sort of clock watching in those days, whatever your job was you finished }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  that day and looked back on it to see if it was worth looking at. And none of that happens today. You just stop and go home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you feel towards your employers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well you felt that they - I mean - how can I tell you this? You felt that you were being given a privilege by working for him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you feel towards your work, did you like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, I was - very happy. Work has never bothered me at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 After you started working part time did it change your attitude to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, it did in a way because, you know, you got very tired working and you couldn\rquote t relax in the same w
ay. And I think that is an advantage today, I mean, that children aren\rquote t forced to - to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 rk and they\rquote 
re more fresh to learn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have any other part time jobs while you were at school that you haven\rquote t mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, I didn\rquote t, I only had the farmer and carrying water to people in the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What was your first full time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh it was going to be a farm labourer for a farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 Well there were two farm wor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 kers, the gras mal and gras bach, th
e little servant and the big servant as it were. And I was passing on my way back from school, I passed the gras mal, the big servant, on this farm and he noticed me and he\rquote 
d probably heard that I was a willing little boy, and he got me there. By the way, there\rquote s the picture of the first f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 ar}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
m I went to, it\rquote s on the wasl. And I\rquote ve just had it actually. That was the furthest farm in the district of the borough of Trawsfynydd. Parish I mean. It was an eight hundred acre farm, you know, with the mountain and ev
erything. It was all in one big lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Well, you know, you learnt to milk, to manage horses. Let me see, I went there - what - I was thirteen in January and I went there in May and started agricultural 
labouring. And I got four pounds ten for the half year, and my keep of course. And I had - good food there too because they kept a housekeeper. They were very easy going kind people and I respect them still. And I\rquote 
ll give one example when I went there to work, everyone cut their own pi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3240317\charrsid11292576 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
ce of bread and butter. The loaf went round the table in those days. There was a sort of understanding in those days that farmers were mean with butter, and you know I was very good at cutting bread, I\rquote d had to learn and then
 so I cut the bread and - I watched the - old bachelor farmer watching me. He was sitting beside me and I put the butter on as I\rquote 
d seen my mother, you know, very thinly. And he picked up the bread and he said, you should put enough butter - more butter on that, you want enough butter so it shows your teeth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3936600\charrsid11292576 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 marks in it. They were very different people to many farmers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How many hours did you work on the f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3936600\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 rm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well it varied. In the summer you see, shearing time and things like that you got up a
t five and you never finished before eight at night. Well you\rquote d never think of finishing before then, you know, after you\rquote d done everything. But I\rquote 
ll tell you a story about this business. There were two bachelors there and I was very friendly with the younger of the two, bachelor farmers, and he was a great chapel goer and he wanted me to come to chapel and I said, oh I\rquote 
m sorry, you know, I can\rquote t. I haven got a suit. I had a pair of shoes. Yes, I had a pair of shoes from my aunt, the one that kept the shop in Traws, I was going to pay after the winter when I\rquote d been paid, pay her. So obviously I couldn
\rquote t afford a suit and the shoes. And shoes were important. I told him you know that my father and mother couldn\rquote t afford a suit for me. But then about two weeks 
later he took me on business with the horse and cart and he went into Dolgellan and straight to Bradleys and he asked the manager, have you got any suits? And I mean the place was full of suits, but it was just a way of talking. And he said, I want a suit
 for this boy. Just as if I was his own boy. And the bought the suit for me. I remember it today, it had two buttons here just below the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3936600\charrsid11292576 k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 nee. And he asked the manager how much hit was and he said, thirty five. And he told me that - I could pay you know aft
er the winter term. But then at the end of the winter term he gave me four pounds ten, and I said to him, look Richard, you haven\rquote t - you know - taken for the suit. How much was it, he said to me. Oh, thirty-five bob. Oh, he said, never mind, you
\rquote ve been a good boy. So I got the suit on top of the four pounds ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you work on Sundays on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, I did. It didn\rquote 
t make any difference but still it was only in necessities we did on Sunday. You know, we fed the animals and that was about all. Because what happened was that Sunday started about four o\rquote clock on Saturday and we\rquote 
d try and get everything finished, especially in the winter, by about five on Saturday and then Sunday would start off that. And we\rquote d oil our work shoes on Saturday ni
ght. And then, you know, the older people would shave on Saturday night and - you know - to save doing it on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you ever have a half day at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, we didn\rquote t, not half days but we did get this week off that I was telling you about.
 But say there was something at home say and you asked you know if you could go home tomorrow you know they\rquote d let you go. And nobody said anything to you. And then of course you\rquote d do extra things you know for that day that you had off.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You said you got four pounds ten, did you feel that this was fair?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I thought it was good because - you see - I\rquote d been working for nothing before I became a farm labourer and I didn\rquote 
t get a single penny for it. Only the potatoes and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you give this money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh yes. Yes, usually I did. I remember in the first term - and I remember - it was - you know, it was time to pay the rent or something and times were hard and she\rquote d ask me to lend her a pound or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3936600\charrsid11292576 ten bob and maybe I\rquote d ask the ma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ster for - you know - a pound or ten bob at the end of the season and you know, that\rquote 
s - you know nearly all your money went to your parents. But then you know we did have to keep ourselves, buy a pair of shoes or something like that. But I\rquote ll tell you
 this, you know, in the second season, the winter season, I remember there was an old - shoe - maker who lived nearby who made homemade shoes as it were. Home shoes. And I fancied a pair of these home shoes but they were three pounds ten or three pounds f
ifteen. So I mean it was hopeless. So I started collecting moles and skinning them and I\rquote d dry the skins at the back of the stable door. Have you ever seen one? They\rquote re very sweet you know. And it\rquote 
s the easiest thing to skin but goodness me does it smell. And in fact I got more money for selling the mole skins than I did from working. And I sold the skins you see to the next door farmer and he\rquote 
d give me two and three or two and nine for skins. So I got my home shoes, and I had about a pound to spare. And you know things like that, like mole catching, well - you know, apart from it keeping you alive it kept you out of misch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3936600\charrsid11292576 ie}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 f and wickedness. You had something to occupy yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you get on with the people you worked with on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, first class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did your employers treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh excellent, excellent. As their own child. And you know you wouldn\rquote 
t say that there was a - a servant and a - a maid there, or housekeeper as she was. As there is ordinarily, you know a housekeeper. And this another thing that the housekeeper taught me, I\rquote 
d taken my clothes off, my new suit in fact and I just slung it down on the c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3936600\charrsid11292576 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
air in the bedroom and she came after me on Monday morning, she said, come here. She said, go up to the bedroom and stow
 away your suit. And you know, fold the trousers along the cease and I mean you know I still do that today now you know I know how to fold them along the creases and I always do. And this is what I was saying about learning things when you\rquote 
re young, you never forget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you feel towards the farm work itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh I was in my element.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did this full time job change your attitude towards the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I mean there was no - talk of the school after that, I mean, it was work from now 
on. The Sunday school was the only school you had after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When did you start this job on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How many years did you do it for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I was there for five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh I changed to another f
arm then. But I was not happy there so I went back to the original one for a year. But you know wages were what were pulling me then. And - on - on this second farm I went to, but the food wasn\rquote 
t any good you know and after one season, winter season, I went back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you go to the quarry after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, I didn\rquote 
t. I was home for a bit and then - no, I went over to the other side of Blaenau to work on a farm and I went to the quarry after that. I went to the quarry when I was eighteen or something. And I came to this area to live, we left Trawsfynydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you do after you left the quarry, did you get your farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I was never very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 fon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 d of the quarry you know. It was only really the hours and the - the money I went for. Getting 
half day on Saturday. But you know farming was my life really. But getting your foot on the right step was the biggest obstacle. And well when did I le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3936600\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ve the quarry? Well I was married when I used to work in the quarry and in fact up \lquote til then hadn\rquote t real
ly considered leaving. But then Hafodfawr Farm became empty and it was a Forestry holding and I borrowed fifty - fifty pounds and went there. And that\rquote 
s really when we started off on our own footing, and things came after that - I mean it was a very hard world. But then, you know, at least you felt you were working for yourself and you took more interest in things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Would you have liked to have a different occupation at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, I wouldn\rquote t. You know - I don\rquote t know you know if I was asked if I wanted to re-start I don\rquote 
t think I would. The only thing I would like to do if I could restart was learnt to play the organ. Yes, I really would like that, or play the piano or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You didn\rquote t serve an apprenticeship or anything like that did you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no. It was farm work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you belong to a trade union or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
No, no, not at that time, not until I went to the quarry. But you know from the quarry onwards yes I have. I was the Secretary of the union in the quarry for a time, for a season or so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 When did you go and work in the Forestry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh - in 1932 I went to the Forstry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And then what did you do, come back to the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - no, I worked in the Forestry \lquote til 1942 and then we got our own farm. We took T
yuococh on rent, you know, we rented tyuococh first and then we bought it in 1946. And then you know things picked up a bit and things came on quite well after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you take part in any of the trade unions activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well not very much. I 
was the Secretary as I told you but I was corresponding with H.T. Edwards at that time. Who was the - District representative or something. And I}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 often felt }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 that if you had a good case he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 dealt with it immediately, but if you didn\rquote 
t have a case I felt he could - distinguish between things that were absolutely necessary, a case that were genuine and the ones that weren\rquote t. I mean if they listened to every complaint they\rquote 
d never get anywhere. And you know if somebody complained that something was wrong and I\rquote d write away to him and he might not take any notice at all. And another thing - you know - I\rquote d write away about something else and he\rquote 
d jump to it immediately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Would you say that workers and employers had the same interests in society or whether they had different interests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well to me they had very different interests, \lquote cos you know, I mean, well I\rquote 
m a teetotaler and I never went to the pub, I never even fancied a pub, you see, my interests were different. I don\rquote t know why or anything though. We
ll maybe it was because I went out in the country to do agricultural work and I never got a chance to get hold of boys who wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
ld go drinking with me. Yes, But I know, I would say that the interests of young boys is really the same in every age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was there any difference between the way the employers see the world and the way workers see the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh yes, yes, there was a difference. Actually I think the employers often feel that they get a worse deal than the workers are getting, even though they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576  we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 re in a much better position, they a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 lways feel that they\rquote re being c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
rossed fantastically because the worker has too much money or something. You can guarantee he\rquote s probably getting less than anybody else is anyway.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Would you say that within the workers of the country that there are divisions of interest?;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - there were some who were very clever, say in the quarry, who\rquote d argue a point with you and, you know, you\rquote 
d think that they were - you know, absolute Tories, but then they\rquote d only be arg
uing the point, and they would be clever enough to do that. But you know they were Labour to the last. And that would happen sometimes just in order to start an argument, but you had to be a clever man to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you feel that there was a difference between craftsmen and workers in the quarry or in the farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well there was a lot more in the quarry than on the farms. Because you see farm work isn\rquote t really divided up into craftsman
\rquote s work and labourer\rquote s work \lquote cos you know if you\rquote re a farm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 worker you\rquote ve learnt - you
\rquote ve learnt the job and you do all - all of it you know. It\rquote s a sort of a whole job. But you see if you\rquote re a rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 man in the quarry you\rquote re - you know, you\rquote re either just a rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 man or you
\rquote re a labourer. And you stay a labourer because at that time you know it was very difficult to move above.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you feel about this distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I\rquote 
ll tell you. There was a manager that came to the Oakleys once when I was working there and you know when he came there were boys going 
home with say twenty-two pounds - twenty two pounds at the end of the month when they got the bonus on top of their basic - basic wages that they got every week. And other boys would be going home with three pounds - three pounds to four pounds each and y
ou know that\rquote s all that the - the - bonus pay was for them. And the manager came there and he said, I\rquote ve got to raise the wages of that man but I can\rquote t do that without taking that person\rquote s wages down. And that didn\rquote 
t really go down very well with people who
 were working on good slates. But I thought you know that he really was one of the fairest men that I ever worked for. Because it really was unfair because - I mean the man who was say working with the - the waste rock was keeping the quarry going just as
 
much as the ones that were actually working on the good seams of rock and bringing the slate up. But, you know, he suffered fantastically in terms of wages and you know I really felt that less of a distinction should be made between these two groups and y
ou know well I work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 ed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 in the Oakleys for about seven or eight years and - and I only worked one month by the day as it were and the sort of basic wage, day wage. This is - that was a very new thing for us because you kno}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  in the other wuarries on the other 
side, you know, if you were on day - day wages you were on day wages and that was it. But you see, if you were in the Oakleys generally you got this bonus at the end of the month, which is a help really. And I think, you know, that this man was - you know
 - I mean he wasn\rquote 
t a Socialist or anything but he was one of the - the greatest sort of reformers of the wage system. And I mean, that was sort of nearest to Socialism to me because this man saw that there was such a - a wrong being done. In his own quarry.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 This was a time then when they brought in the idea of a small bargain which the price of bonus for a month was negotiated on }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 the b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 asis of the nature of the rock, and if you were working on very good rock your wages, per pound of slate produced came
 down and if you were working on very bad rock the pay per pound of slate produced went up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, that\rquote s - yes, that\rquote s it. And the thing was I mean he did what he could, this manager and he obviously he couldn
\rquote t pay twenty pounds to everybody. Bu
t - so he brought the sort of twenty pound people down to about thirteen and the others might get say five, six or seven pounds. Yes, seven pounds was often the - the money you got at the end of the month, the bonus. And you know I respected anything abou
t this man. The other thing is you know - you had to have labourers in a quarry and - I think you know our education system has done completely drunk. Not that I\rquote m against - education at all. But try and teach a boy of eighteen years old and you
\rquote ll never teach him because his learning time is gone. I mean teach him a craft, to do work. Not that I want it to go back to having fourteen year old boys doing man\rquote s work for pitiful wages. But I don\rquote 
t really believe in - raising the school leaving age. Because there\rquote s no point in giving people education unless there\rquote s say a potenti}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 l for learning there. And I think the country\rquote s really lost it\rquote s feet over this. I mean it\rquote s done so much money on education. But you know if you want to go ahead I mean there\rquote s a chance 
for you to go ahead, but you know, I mean, from the education party all the way you know, but to give it to people who want education rather than to everybody. But for instance, you know, say somebody has passed his B.A. or something, well I wouldn
\rquote t like - I really don\rquote t want it to be the case that - that the person with the B.A. is - earning half - half his wages, I mean, that\rquote 
s completely wrong. And the other thing that I think is very unfair, you get people today shouting about things, people who are ea
rning thirty pounds a week, when the postmen are on strike. I mean, why should the postmen deliver letters to people who are earning thirty pounds a week and why should the coal miners go and get into the coalmines just to get cheap coal for us, for me. A
nd why should a - a farm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
worker, you know, work on a farm on the cheap just to produce cheap food for people who earning more - even forty pounds, there are plenty of them today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Would you say that your full time job changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well the thing was that when you went to be a farm worker you felt that you\rquote d become a man over night, and probably too much so.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 After you left school you went to live on the farms didn\rquote t you, you didn\rquote t live at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh no, no, I didn\rquote t, only occasionally. Yes, say I\rquote d go for half a year to - to the farm and - once in that half year I
\rquote d come back for a weekend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did full time work change your relationship with your parents at all? Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
No, not at all. Except that it sort of put you slightly apart from them, separated you from them physically. And of course you were more pleased to see them and have their company afterwards when you saw them again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did the way in which you spent your Sundays change at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well you had to do some work, we - your share of the work on the farm was still there on a Sunday. But only absolutely necessary things.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And you still went to the chapel and Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes. I mean chapel was part of your week, it wasn\rquote t really a full week unless you\rquote d been to chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you start to take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, I think I did. Yes, I began to realize and I still realize this all through the years, the great wrong
 that was done to my parents. I mean, you know, I realized that}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 - you know, something had to be done to improve things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What were your political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - I thought there was too big a gap most of all. But you know I\rquote ve never been in that pa
rty that wants you and me to be on the same level - or us and them to be on the same level. I think it would be a very - unsavoury society where everybody was on exactly the same level. I mean, that\rquote 
s my view. But you know I want everybody to have a living wage, whatever that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Have you any idea why you felt this way, what made you feel like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I don\rquote t know because I wasn\rquote 
t a great reader, I used to like to read and I used to read quite a bit you know before we had televisions, but since the television I haven\rquote 
t read very much at all, but I think you know a lot of it was got from my father. Because my father had worked a very hard period.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You were too young to vote in the 1919 general election?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, I think it was 1930 or 1931 when I first voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember feeling under any pressure from anybody to vote for any particular political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, I didn\rquote t - I didn\rquote t feel any of this pressure because everybody knew me and - I mean, you know, and they knew whic
h direction I was going, and once I made up my mind that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You didn\rquote t feel any pressure from your employer at all to vote in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, not at all. But I do know that some farmers did do this and - Liberalism was all the rage then an
d - and lots of farmers felt there was nothing else other than Liberalism and encouraged the people to vote Liberal and applied pressure. But generally they didn\rquote t apply pressure on you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Were you ever a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, I was but not at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 But you did after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was it the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, in fact I was Chairman of the local Labour party when they first chose T.W.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Nones and the Parliamentary candidate for the first time. I just happened to be the Chairman, and I felt very proud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 So you worked for the Labour party at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes I did. Yes, I didn\rquote t make any great fuss, I just worked quietly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you take part in any political activities apart from at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, I did. Yes, when I was Chairman I didn\rquote t miss - I didn\rquote t miss a single meeting of the local Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you change the way that you spent your leisure time at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well the thing was that when I was young things were very different from what they are today. For one night you might work \lquote 
til ten o\rquote clock but generally it was eight o\rquote clock. But if you wanted to go you were allowed to go and there\rquote d be no loss of wages or anything. Yes, it was - it was - a question of the discretion of your employer really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you start going out more at night after you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes. Particularly because in the area where I lived people were very kind and you\rquote 
d be in one place tonight and say another place the next night. But in the summer season you\rquote d be home because you\rquote d be working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you go out with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh yes, I did, I went out with friends. But the trouble was that a lot of my friends were young boys and they were very keen on - on drinking. But you know I never - I never touched it at all. I hate it, I don\rquote 
t know why. And I mean, you know, it wasn\rquote t that my father and mother sort of forbade it or anything because I knew my father liked his pint and that was it. Once a month or something like that he\rquote d have one. But I can\rquote 
t really tell you why I went so much against drink. But I suppose it was really in this area where people were strong chapel goers and - therefore sober. For instance, I was friends with a boy from Blaenou and I was really 
good friends, like two brothers, this was when I went to work at the agricultural labourer in Blaunau and he liked his pint and he\rquote d say, come for a pint with me. No I won\rquote t come, I said. He\rquote d say - I\rquote 
d say to him, you go, but if you\rquote re not back in five minutes I\rquote ll be gone. But you know since then I\rquote ve thought about it a bit more. It seemed amazing that he was able to drink the pint in five minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you make a lot of new friends, girls and boys, during this time just after you\rquote d left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 O
h yes, I did, naturally I mixed with the same type, the same age group as myself and I was fantastically popular. I was quite a character at making - fun and things like that. And - you know, so I became a sort of character.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you come to meet these boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I mean there really wasn\rquote 
t anything else, you - you had to entertain yourself with a crowd. You had to make your own fun in those days. We\rquote d go out to sing and fool around and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you take your new friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes I did. And her}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 \rquote s another thing, after we started going around with girls my mother and father liked it better if we brought her - the girls home. And they\rquote d never say anything to us as long as we took her home, even if we
\rquote d changed her by the end of the week. Only they like}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 d to see her and they welcomed e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
ach one of them. Because my brother at that time was a hell of a first and he\rquote d bring twenties of them back and my mother\rquote d say sometimes, oh, I wonder who were going to get next week. And that was a fact.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was there anywhere special that you went with your special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well not really, we would go to an eistedford. But then I never really was a wild eistedford goer, I wasn\rquote 
t that keen. And then of course there was the chapel, because that was the main centre. And
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And that\rquote 
s where you met your friends very often or saw them? You said your parents liked to see your friends, but did they expect to know where you were when you went out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, they - no, they\rquote d much rather you say, well I\rquote m going to so and so or so and so and - or I\rquote 
ve got a date here or there. They\rquote d much prefer me to say, rather than you were - you being sly. Yes, I mean they encouraged that, you know, you said that you were going her
e or there on a date, and they knew - then they knew you know perfectly well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they expect you to come in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, that was a bit of a rule in the home, you know, all the time. Yes, when we were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 young people we weren\rquote t really much after eleven o\rquote c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ock. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How many servants were there on the farm where you worked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh two. The - gras mal and gras bach. The little servant and the big servant. And then there was a maid or a housekeeper and the two old bachelors. And the - gras mal was - fantastic with me. He was an exceptional man, and it wasn\rquote 
t every - all the time that you\rquote d find people like that. And he taught you to be a good craftsman because he was a - a man who was good at his job, everything had to be just so. And t
his is a thing that he always said, I mean, keep things - put things away in their places and they\rquote ll always be there for you to find them afterwards when you wanted them. That was something that he emphasised greatly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Where did you sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, in the - in the - in the house. Very often I slept with the boss. The two of us - the old bachelor and I, we slept together.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Where did you eat, with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, with the family. The old bachelor and I sat on the other side of the table with each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did the master look a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 ft}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 er you as you were working or did he pass orders to you through the gras mal?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well no, I mean it\rquote s hard to believe this sort of thing but I was part of the family. In fact I was as a son. Yes, we were - so
n and daughter. We just happened to be sort of older sons and daughters. It was just that gap that made us slightly different from a normal family. But there was no - and this is another thing that happened, if the master was invited to another - a farm o
ver there for supper everybody went. There wasn\rquote t a - a servant maid in this area, it just so happened. You were just as a family. And if they came to our house, they\rquote d come as a crowd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you call your masters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh I used to call them - by 
their - by their names - their proper names. Richard and Rees. But you used the instead of tee, using the polite form rather than the familiar one. Yes, yes, I always used the polite form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you think your employers took an interest in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes they did fantastically. Not an educational interest but - they\rquote 
d - took an interest on another level, sort of in my personal character. Yes, you\rquote re character because they wanted you to emerge as a good worker and that was the most important thing for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they give you any moral guidance at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 They were fantastic at telling you - not - not rea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ly moral guidance, they didn\rquote t preach }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7297443\charrsid11292576 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 you but they were keen chapel goers and they expected the chapel to do that job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have any free time in which you were free to go and do what you wanted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, exactly as if I was at home. You know, there wasn\rquote 
t a master and servant relationship there. I mean, you know, you had to do exactly what the master said but you did have your own judgement as well that was taken into account. I\rquote 
ll tell you what happened quite often, I was extremely keen on fishing. And - one of the bachelors was really keen on fish, he\rquote d eat fish for every meal if he could, and so sometimes I\rquote d escape and
 go fishing and as long as I bought eight or nine fishes back with me nothing would be said. \lquote Cos he got what he liked and I\rquote d done what I liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 They didn\rquote t mind you leaving the house and going out if you wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, not at all. And I\rquote ll tell you about one particular night. When I arrived home and went to bed at six o\rquote 
clock in the morning. And as a rule we didn\rquote t get up \lquote til about half past seven in the winter and I went to bed next to the old bachelor and I thought he hadn\rquote t heard me and as soon as I\rquote d settled down he said to me, it\rquote 
s time to get up. And he got up and I had to get up too. This was in order to teach me to get - get to bed earlier. So it made me go - go to bed early that night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you feel homesick at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, I was an extremely homesick person. Because - say I\rquote d been home for a weekend or something, well I\rquote 
d be really homesick for a couple of days, and then it was O.K.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was this because you lacked friends and companions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - no, I mean there wasn\rquote t real}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11687285\charrsid11292576 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 y much choice in those days in that area. You had to become part of the community. Otherwise you\rquote d be completely out of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was there anything about your work that you particularly liked or disliked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well, there were things that you
 preferred. I mean I liked working the horses for instance. Going out and - and ploughing when I was about a fifteen year old boy and - I\rquote d think about it even when I was in bed, about beginning this ploughing. But once you\rquote 
d started it was O.K. You were happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did the housework go, did the maid do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
How the housekeeper did, but I had to do a lot of it. The churning and those sort of things. And feeding the calves and things. But the housekeeper worked very hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she do the washing and mend and make all the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, everything. But I\rquote d take my clothes home usually, my rough clothes. I mean, we didn\rquote 
t have - underwear then. I just had a shirt and - and things, I mean, that was really all I had and - I used to take them back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Who did the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh the housekeeper did all that. And we were lucky \lquote 
cos it was a place where they killed two pigs every year and these were big ones two, and they\rquote d kill a bullock every year, and they salted them. And there was plenty of oatmeal there but they didn\rquote t - and they didn\rquote 
t have to buy anything really very much, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6629670\charrsid11292576 only}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 sugar and tea and they bought that by the sack and tea by the chest. So I mean the housekeeper had plenty of things for her work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 There weren\rquote t any children at the farm were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
No, only the two old bachelors. So I was really the baby. And they took to me fantastically and I was only really about as high as the table when I went there to work first. Yes, that was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ig table, I could just see over the top of it. And I - you know, I got such a good place to go and work for first of all that I went ahead like lightning.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Where did the family eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh everything was in the kitchen on a big white table. And there was never a table c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 oth or anything on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What sort of cooking equipment did they have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh they had a peat fire, it was all peat. Yes, I mean - they only had peat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they have an oven by the side of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, they had a - a big oven to bake in. Yes, it was an oven by itself with a - with a fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You mean a fire under it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
No, the fire was actually in it. They called it a brick oven and you filled it with fire until it was white hot and put the bread in and - and shut it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What time did you have breakfast there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well after we\rquote d finished giving food to all the animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was everyone in the family present?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, yes, they all were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did you usually have to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well actually you could say that every meal was the same, breakfast, dinner, tea and supper. They were all the same. You\rquote 
d get brewer for breakfast in the winter. That\rquote s hot stock poured over oatmeal. And then for - for dinner we\rquote d have bacon, salted bacon and - and fresh meat on Sundays. But it was still salted meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What time did you have your other meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - dinner was at twelve o\rquote clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well - it really depended on what was on the go at the moment, but somewhere between four and five. But I\rquote ll tell you what 
happened, I don\rquote t know if you\rquote ve seen something similar to this before, they\rquote d make oatmeal in a big - oak chest and they\rquote d fill that up with the oatmeal and then they\rquote d salt a pig and they\rquote 
d put the hams and the shoulders }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 nto the oatmeal to keep the, the
y buried them in it. Well they were worth eating. It was first class for flavour, and I think it even gave some flavour to the oatmeal. Yes, the two things worked together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they make bread and jam and bottled fruit and vegetables and pickles at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well it depen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ed very much on who the housekeeper was. Yes, and there were - but there were plenty of bilberries there and those were made into jam, they weren\rquote t bottled, they didn\rquote 
t bottle much in those days. Because bottlings a pretty new thing really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about wine or beer, did they ever make any of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, they had a few remedies - sort of home }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 remed}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they grow fruit or vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, they g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 rew potatoes and carrots and sw}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 edes and they even planted cabbages you know as they got older. \lquote Cos in the first world war you had to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they buy any vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh very little. And, you know - in the summer say we\rquote d make - two pots of butter, you know, \lquote 
cos the - the cows would be milking well. And one of those would do for the winter because we kept - we kept young cows that had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 \rquote t already calved - heifer cows, in the winter \lquote cos it saved work, and nothing much was - was sold in the winter at all, not even animals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Who did the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - it wasn\rquote t really a garden, it was just an enormous big area with sheep everywhere. And nobody\rquote 
d really take a-y interest in closing any bit off to make a garden. I didn\rquote t see a garden as long as I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 They didn\rquote t have any tinned fruit or anything did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What animals did you have on the farm?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh - sheep and cows. Yes, we bred cows.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, only for their own use though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, but only for their own use again. But they sold sheep and sold wood and sold cattle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was it you and the two old bachelors who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, well - no - well it was me and one of them, the younger one. One of them was a bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 gallivanted}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576  and bit more of a gentleman than the other and he wasn\rquote t home very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How many times a week would you have meat to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh every day, every day. Bacon that is and salted beef on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you have the same meals as the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes, everything was exactly the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember anything that the family did on a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 istmas Day or a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well not birthdays. I mean Christmases depended very much on what work was on the go at the moment. But maybe there\rquote 
d be a sort of get together with two or three families. Maybe up to a week after Christmas and they\rquote d eat a goose, and we\rquote d have a first class dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about musical instruments and singing, was there any of this in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Oh yes, one housekeeper who came there, she was very nice, I got on with her very well, she bought her organ, she could play the organ very well. We went down to Llanfachreth in the horse and cart to fet
ch the organ and were so pleased with it and it meant a whole day to get it and she had a fiddle too, a violin. And she was there for about a year and a half, we had a very interesting and amusing time with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Was anyone there together singing or listening to the singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes. But they weren\rquote t themselves - they weren\rquote 
t musicians but they liked singing Listening to singing that is, but they weren\rquote t musicians.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember there being books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well very very few. There were a few - Bibles and religious books but that\rquote s all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they have newspapers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, they had just one. Banner. Y Baner. The Banner, or Flag.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No magazines or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you ever remember anyone reading aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No. Not - no - on the other farm, the next door farm though they kept - they had prayer readings. And I\rquote 
ll tell you something that happened at the other farm. I was a boy. It was one of the times when we were swapping with each other to gather the sheep, you know how they do today. We\rquote 
d gone early in the morning to this farm to gather the sheep and they were just about to start the prayer reading. And the bible was going round the table and everyone was reading a few verses and the old
 man was saying the prayers. And there was a boy there who was a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 scyther}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
, he was only there for the summer, and - this morning the Bible fell into the hands of this boy and we were all sitting round this table, the - old man at the end and his son in t
he middle and the syther next to him and I was like the visitor and this scyther thought he was too clever and thought he\rquote d be able to avoid reading the verses. And he said to this family, totally Welsh family, he said, I can\rquote 
t read Welsh Mr - I can only r
ead English. And he thought he was clear. And he said to his daughter, Elizabeth Anne, go and - go and get the English Bible, the great King understands English as well as he does Welsh. Although none of them understood English. And so the scyther had to 
read a - two or three English verses every time the Bible came round to him. But I\rquote ve never seen anyone put down as smartly as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember a funeral at all in this family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, stra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 gely enough I don\rquote t. I don\rquote t even remember a - a funeral in that area during the time that I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you go out with the old man at all for weekends or Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No never. Only - only say taking the sheep or the cattle to the market. And I used to drive the cattle to the fair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did you like going wi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 th him}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I wasn\rquote t that keen, I didn\rquote t like fairs that much. I liked a quieter life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your masters think it was wrong to play or do any work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well the thing was he didn\rquote t do it himself so he didn\rquote t encoura
ge you to. I mean, the things was you had to do the necessities, but I used to escap}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 to go fishing sometimes on a Sunday. And I remember getting caught and I got a good lecture. I remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, they were very kee
n chapel goers. It took about half an hour and ten minutes to get there and half an hour and ten minutes to get back. And I mean it was walking in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did the servants go to the same chapel as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes, they did. And they sat on the same seat too. In the chapel. There was no difference, he was incredible that way. I\rquote 
m sure it would look very odd today. And that\rquote s a loss to us. I mean if a stranger, a visitor, a man had come to the chapel I mean they\rquote d have immediately assumed that I was the son of my employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about prayers in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, but there was an occasional - meeting for prayers. They didn\rquote 
t have the morning prayers like the other farm did but the preacher would come by sometimes. I mean - you know, they were quite Christian in their way but they were - they were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 n\rquote }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 t like the other people who were sort of crazy the other way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your masters take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, he didn\rquote t. Nobody took much interest in politics at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 You don\rquote t know how he voted or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh well I\rquote m sure he was a Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did your master take part in any sports, go to races, play cards or go to clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 The only thing was that one of them was quite a good - shooter. But the other one didn\rquote 
t really take much interest in anything outside his work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you ever remember either of the old men going away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, well I told you that one of them went sometimes he\rquote d go away for a fortnight to his aunt or cousin, but the other didn
\rquote t, I mean the younger of the two. Very - he went very very little.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did it make any difference if the elder one went away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, you were more free in a way, because younger one and me we - well we were really like two brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did the master\rquote s friends come and stay in the house or eat in the house at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, they did, especially in summer. A lot came over to gather the sheep and others to fish. And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 everybody got a meal, whoever he was, and a lot of preachers came t
here in the summer. And because the preacher was considered to be a sort of little Jesus Christ he got special treatment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they come over to help with the shearing and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh - oh yes, I mean they swapped over - in the shearing time. And - it\rquote 
s a pity you know that a lot of this has been lost now. They was a great sort of community feeling. Neighbourliness then. And if somebody was ailing or something was wrong, I mean everyone\rquote 
d be there to help. And you know I mean for the shearing there were eight hundred sheep at Allt Lwyd and there were about twelve hundred in the farm next to us. I mean you know if you tried to shear them on your own well you couldn\rquote 
t gather them for a start on your own because of the big fridd, the area of rough past
ure between the hayfields and the mountains, well that was three hundred acres, the fridd alone. And what could you do in a place like that without help. And another thing they did was to cut peat together. And they\rquote d do it say for three days, they
\rquote d be three days in one place and three days in another. I don\rquote t know if you\rquote ve seen people cutting peat before. Yes, you\rquote d get six of them going forward in a line, you know, there were six men always in this line and they
\rquote d go forward together. They\rquote d have prepared it you know, cut some of it the day before then they\rquote 
d dig out this time, the next day. And - and they threw the - the squares of peat out to the side. And you were arranged along this line in order of strength so the weakest of the youngest would be nearest to the heap of peat that was being produced.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
Would you say that the people who came to visit your master were of the same class or group as him, were they the same type of people as him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes. But - if anything they were a bit more snobbish
. They were farmers but - I mean he was a big farmer but he was a type of man who was fantastically close to you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What class would you say he came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - middle class you\rquote d call it in one way. But after all he - you know - in the end he wa
s a worker. He was a first class worker.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Would you say that both of them were the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - well the older one, he wasn\rquote t - he wasn\rquote t quite - quite the same. He was a bit of a dealer and he\rquote 
d do anything rather than work and he was a bit of a devil that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did they treat some friends differently from others, did they show more respect to some more than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 The family in the next farm to us, they were incredibly close together. They were more than friends, beyond friends. They
 were like relatives, although they weren\rquote t related at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did the visitors to your master\rquote s house behave towards the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well I\rquote ll tell you exactly how it was. I was a servant, I was there five years - in fact over five years. And if
 somebody ignored me, well - that was the end of it for him. He was nothing, he was out of it altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember any of the visitors treating you differently from your master?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, they did, they tried. And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 very often it was the preachers that did that but I mean they didn\rquote 
t please at all by doing that. And the thing was they treated the housekeeper well, she was a young girl, well she was a little bit different. But they did try to ignore me. Specially the young preachers. And they\rquote d
 come and tye often wanted me out of the way so that they could talk to the housekeeper. And they\rquote d try and push me out. But as soon as they did that I mean I was more determined to stay, it made me a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 gry, and the people wo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
ld tell them immediately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you think your m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 sters\rquote  were satisfied with their station in life, their position in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, yes, they were, they were fantastically satisfied with their life. They were thankful. They didn\rquote 
t want to climb up any further. No, they were - happy as long as things were paying their way they were all right. They were fantastically nice people like that. I mean say something died, well they didn\rquote 
t like seeing anything die, but I mean, you know, there was no fuss, it just stopped there and that was it. I mean I expect the thing was that they\rquote d had a hard life at first and they\rquote 
d come up a bit and become pretty successful people, and you know therefore they were satisfied with their lives, because things were going pretty well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Had you met people like your masters before you went to work there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, well I - I never knew anyone like him afterwards. I mean people to work for. They were fantastic people. Because I mean you didn
\rquote t feel - well - the thing was after I left there and I went to anot
her farm and that opened my eyes to what a farm labourer was generally. We had different food, half the food, worse food. Because, you know, the - the old people had - I mean, any time you wanted food you could go to the drawer, \lquote 
cos the food was kept in a drawer then - the drawer of the bi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5254899\charrsid11292576 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
 white table and I mean you know there was - bread and butter and milk and - and anything you wanted and you could have it at any time of the day. But this was quite different from the other farm - the other farms.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 I suppose you weren\rquote t part of the family there or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, not at all, it was completely different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 How did you feel towards the way of life that your master had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 I envied him greatly. And I think he was worth envying and looking
 up to. For the reason that he treated his servant like a man and not like a servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Would you say that their manners and ways of behaviour were different from those of the people you\rquote d mixed with before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, it was different, they were more direct. If you didn\rquote t please them they\rquote 
d let you know. And in a way they were more harsh, \lquote cos you know if you didn\rquote t please they\rquote d tell you plainly. You know, go away and don\rquote t do that again or don\rquote t come here again. Because I mean you know the boss could 
- hurt you if you didn\rquote t behave.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did your oldest sister do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well she became a maid in the first season. But her ambition was to be a nurse. But she wasn\rquote 
t able to do that, she got married pretty young but you know to be a nurse was her ambition. And she\rquote d have made a good nurse too, she\rquote d have been in her element.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she work at all after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 No, no, she\rquote s got a full house - about four - four children and she hasn\rquote 
t got time. And then she went to Liverpool and she kept a sort of lodging house where teachers and people like that stayed all the time. And what\rquote 
s funny is that - two other sons have married teachers, in fact, three of the boys in our family have married teachers. And this was teachers who used to stay with the
m in Liverpool and they were all Welsh teachers too. They were girls from Wales. Who had gone to work in Liverpool. Yes, they\rquote d gone to work in Liverpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about your older brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 My oldest brother, I wouldn\rquote t say this if he wasn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 
 a brother to me, but he was inc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 redibly clever. If he\rquote d had an education he\rquote d be some boy I\rquote 
m sure. He was fantastic with workers education. He was fantastic with the union. It\rquote s unusual to meet a boy like him. He was a real scholar, the only thing that I could ou
tshine him at awas at sums and I would do a sum under his nose and he was very mean to me about this.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What actually did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh - well he worked in a quarry. Oh have you heard of Professor Glyn L. Philips on the television? You must have hear
d him talking about science or something. Well my brother\rquote s daughter is the wife of that man, and you know, he\rquote s buried now but if he was alive he\rquote d be very proud of her, the little girl. Oh yes, he\rquote 
d be proud. And she was a teacher, she passed her B.A. in Welsh. Oh yes, he\rquote d be very proud of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 And he was a rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 man in the quarry was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, he was a rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 All his life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, well he - he died when he was forty. Of Silicosis. Yes, I mean he - he\rquote d worked in very confined spaces
 and he was a very hard working boy. And my father even died at sixty-two and he was an enormously big man but I was lucky to get out of that place, otherwise you know I\rquote m sure I\rquote 
d be dead by now. Every man who worked with me in the quarry - each one of them's dead now. Every one jack of them. The people on the same bench as me. I mean the same floor, the same level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about Glyn, what was his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 I don\rquote t know. Glyn would have been a musician if he\rquote d stuck to it. He was a good musician. I re
member he bought a piano and we\rquote d come to live in this area and he\rquote d gone to work in Bryn Rodyn and by this time he was getting quite good money as a farm worker. He was in a pretty good position though. Oh yes, and he decided to }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 buy this piano on insta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 lments. But then things went worse and - my mother and f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 ather ended up paying the insta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 lments and - my sister\rquote 
s got it now. Well he got pleasure from it. And my younger sister got piano lessons and learnt to play the piano on it. And - my father would always say though that Glyn was a much better musician that you Betty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Do you remember going to see Glyn at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes I do. Well - well Glyn and Molly his wife lived there on his own. And both of them - I mean, Molly could play the piano, nearly a}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 nything really. And - but Glyn w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
ould criticize her and then it would get bad between them. Yes, I mean Glyn would be - would have been a - a musician if he\rquote d stuck to it. And he liked singing too but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What work did he do in the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well - he went t
o the quarries first but - he was with the farmers for a long time. He really liked it with the farmers. That was after he\rquote 
d failed in the quarry. And he ended up as the Registrar. Of births and deaths. Marriages and things. And - and - well he was a part 
time Registrar by the end of his life. Glyn was a good scholar you know. Because - you see, Glyn was the first one of us to get secondary education and he went to what was the A grade then, but you see the three oldest ones, I mean it was work for us. But
 you know Glyn got one or two years in the A grade, and I mean he was about fourteen when he went there. I mean he was - so he was what fifteen or sixteen when he started working. And my youngest sister was a good scholar too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What did she do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 She was a - a typist and - well I mean her husband\rquote s }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 de}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 ad now. Well - but she wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16590743\charrsid11292576 s married for what - about - fo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 
rty years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Did she do any work after she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Oh yes, she worked all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 As a typist?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Yes, typing. In, you know, different places. I mean she should have become a teacher but you know there wasn\rquote 
t an opportunity, I mean, money ruled everything then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15417384 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 What about your sisters\rquote  husband\rquote s, what was their work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12212030 RW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12408339\charrsid11292576 Well my - oldest sister\rquote s husband worked in the quarr
